3. Write a program for creating a pie-chart in R using the input vector(21,62,10,53). 
Provide labels for the chart as ‘London’, ‘New York’, ‘Singapore’, ‘Mumbai’. Add a 
title to the chart as ‘city pie-chart’ and add a legend at the top right corner of the chart.
 program:
 
 # Input vector
data <- c(21, 62, 10, 53)

# Labels for the chart
labels <- c('London', 'New York', 'Singapore', 'Mumbai')

# Create pie chart
pie(data, labels = labels, main = 'City Pie Chart')

# Add legend at top right corner
legend('topright', legend = labels, cex = 0.8, fill = rainbow(length(data)))

